;; task: auto-tune-max-attempts
;; goal: Use evolve-strategy to auto-tune a strategy's max-attempts.
;;       Steps:
;;         1. Define a strategy "tiny" with :max-attempts 2.
;;         2. Run (intend "test-goal" (lambda (g) "") (lambda (c) "fail")
;;              :strategy "tiny") — this will record a failed run.
;;         3. Call (evolve-strategy "tiny") and capture the new name.
;;         4. Read (strategy-field new-name "max-attempts") — should be > 2.
;;         5. Display the new max-attempts as a number.
;; expect: 4
;; hint: After evolve-strategy runs, the new strategy's max-attempts
;;       will be the old + 2 (capped at 20) because success-rate < 0.5
;;       AND avg-attempts = old max-attempts.
;; hint: Use (define new-name (evolve-strategy "tiny")) to capture
;;       the new strategy name returned as a string.
;; hint: (strategy-field new-name "max-attempts") returns an integer.
;; hint: The full sequence:
;; hint:   (define-strategy "tiny" "(dummy)" :max-attempts 2)
;; hint:   (intend "goal"
;; hint:          (lambda (g) "")
;; hint:          (lambda (c) "fail")
;; hint:          :strategy "tiny")
;; hint:   (define new (evolve-strategy "tiny"))
;; hint:   (display (strategy-field new "max-attempts"))
;; depend: edsl
